args.new_str:
# Convert to 0-based index and patch layer
    layer_idx = layer_id - 1
    layer = layers[layer_idx]
    mp.enable_vit_custom_block(layer, layer_idx)

    # Ensure output directory exists
    os.makedirs(savedir, exist_ok=True)

    # Save input parameters for reproducibility
    inputs = {
        "layer_id": layer_id,
        "savedir": savedir,
        "model_family": model_family,
        "model_size": model_size
    }
    input_path = os.path.join(savedir, f"run_exp1_inputs_layer_{layer_id}.pkl")
    with open(input_path, "wb") as f:
        pickle.dump(inputs, f)

    # Load and preprocess a sample image
    img_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), "assets", "bird.png")
    img = Image.open(img_path)
    img = val_transform(img).unsqueeze(0).cuda()

    # Forward pass to capture features
    with torch.no_grad():
        _ = model(img)

    # Extract absolute feature activations
    feat_tensor = layer.feat
    feat_abs = feat_tensor.abs()

    # Save feature activations
    feat_path = os.path.join(savedir, f"feat_abs_layer_{layer_id}.pkl")
    with open(feat_path, "wb") as f:
        pickle.dump(feat_abs.numpy(), f)

    # Generate and save 3D visualization
    lib.plot_3d_feat_vit(feat_tensor, layer_idx, model_family, model_size, savedir)
